		"body": "Fixes : #14223 \r\n## AI Assistance Disclosure\r\n\r\nAI tools were used to help identify the root cause and suggest the fix. I have reviewed all the code, understand each change, and verified it works correctly.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nThe `ERRORS_NOTE_NAME` constant in `section.rs` had UTF-8 encoding corruption, displaying garbled characters instead of the intended emoji. The `RenderFailed` error variant was also accidentally removed in an earlier commit.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nFixed the UTF-8 encoding in `ERRORS_NOTE_NAME` and restored the `RenderFailed` error variant. Added a test to verify that importing a truncated `.one` file returns a clear error message.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\nAdded `convert_truncated_file_returns_error` in `renderer/tests/convert.rs`. Added `test-data/broken_truncated.one` (first 100 bytes of `ink.one`) as test data.\r\ncargo test --test convert\r\n\r\nAll 5 tests pass.",
